{
  "stem": "10181.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, by the police.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "On-- on-- on the--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, in the evening.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah, we had to stay there, like I said.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And like I told you before, I woke up in the middle of the night when-- when Francesca came to say goodbye.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then, I know early in the morning, my mother tried to get in touch by phone-- there was a phone in the school, and everyone was lined up to make calls-- to my uncles in Holland.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I had two-- two uncles from my father's side, the two brothers of my father who lived in Holland.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One was Max Spiegel and the other one was Adolf Spiegel.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then I had an aunt, a sister of my mother, who had married a Dutch Jew and lived in a town called Enschede.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And apparently, she must have spoken to him sometime during the day or the next day, I don't quite remember the sequence, and made arrangements for us to go to Gennep, which was the-- Adolf.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was-- Adolf was the oldest brother of my father and had also been my father's partner in-- in the business.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I also remembered him well from-- still from-- from Germany.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The other uncle, I knew him by name, and I'd been to his place in Holland on visit, but I-- I don't remember him from Germany.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He had left much earlier.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So a day or two later-- I-- it could have been a week later, I don't know the exact time-- we were-- went by train to Holland.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You know, it's-- it's a little bit vague.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I don't-- I-- as far as I remember, I went from the school to Holland.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I know that my mother had been-- was allowed back to pick up things.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't think I went back, I don't-- because I don't remember being back in the house.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I'm sure I probably would have remembered it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because everything was smashed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't think there would have been any point to it in any case at that time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She-- this gentleman who lived upstairs, who was an ex-policeman, tried to protect her when she was around, you know, use his influence.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we were taken to Holland by somebody, who I didn't know who it was, but I found out again years later this was a non-Jewish lady who was working as a-- as a maid for a-- for a Jewish family.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she was Dutch, had a Dutch passport or was Dutch.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And she took us across the border.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Basically, illegally.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "A lot of the German Jews tried to cross the border illegally.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And even though the border was closed officially, after the Kristallnacht, the Dutch sort of let people cross and then put them in camps, you know, of their own.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But as we had somewhere to go, we were-- we didn't have to go anywhere.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We went straight to-- to Gennep.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It was like going on a regular trip, basically.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There was no-- no incident, really.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Just my sister and myself, OK, not my mother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She had to-- she remained behind because she was trying to-- like wind up her affairs and-- and get a visa to somewhere, whatever.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because I don't think she wanted to stay in Holland.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't think she could stay in Holland, really.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Dutch didn't-- didn't want you either.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I mean, they'd let you cross the border, but they preferred you to continue from there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Anyway, so--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But when I got to Holland, I knew already that he'd been released.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he arrived maybe-- anything between, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "A couple of weeks to a month later, he arrived also in Gennep, OK, that I remember.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He might-- I think it was a few weeks later.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, train.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By train.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She took us by train.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, she brought us across the border and Adolf met us I think at the first or second station in Holland.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because he-- we-- he lived in a [INAUDIBLE] town called Gennep, which was fairly close to the border, even though it wasn't on the main rail line.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I think he picked up-- us up, if I remember, in a town called Nijmegen, which was-- could have been Nijmegen or Arnhem, one of the-- one-- because both are on the-- on the main railroad.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- and both of them are fairly close to Gennep.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nijmegen is close.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Arnhem is a little bit further away, but also not very far.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he picked us up.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I think we went by bus from there to-- to Gennep.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I didn't mind so much.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My sister did.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
